https://peps.python.org/pep-0008/#naming-conventions
-A variable is created the moment we assign a value to it
  x=5
-Casting: when we want to specify the data type
  str(x)
-We can use doulble or single quote to specify string  
  x="Ayush" or 'Ayush'
-Case Sensitive: x is other variable X is other
  x="something"
  X="something  
-VariableName: 
  --start with a letter or underscore 
    myvar = 1
    _myvar = 2
  --can not start with a number
    1wrong = 1 ><
  --can only contain alphanumeric character or underscore
    a2_var = 1
  --can not be a python keyword
    int = 12 ><
-Multi word variables
  --CAPITALS(constants are written in CAPITALS.)
    THISISAVARIABLE = 0
  --TitleCase(Class names are TilteCase without underscores.)
    ThisIsAVariable = 0
  --camelCase
    thisIsAVariable = 1
  --PascalCase
    ThisIsAVariable = 2
  --snake_case(Variable and function names use lowercase words_separated_by_underscore.)
    this_is_a_variable = 3
-Assign multiple values  
  --many values to multiple variables
    x, y, z = "one", "two", "three"
  --one value to multiple variable
    x = y = z = "one value"
  --unpacking a Collection
    fruits = ["orange", "grape", "kiwi"]
    x, y, z = fruits
    fruits = ("orange", "grape", "kiwi")
    (x, y, z) = fruits
-Output variables
  --we use print
    print(x)
  --multiple variables
    print(x,y,z)
  --or we can use + string will concatinate numbers will add
    print(x+y+z)
-Global variables: use global keyword if you want to change a global variable inside a function.
  --create a variable outside and using it inside the function
    x = "awesome"
    def myfunc():
    print("Python is " + x)
    myfunc()
  --if we create a variable inside the function it will be local and can be only used inside this function scope
    x = "awesome"
    def myfunc():
      x = "fantastic"
      print("Python is " + x) -->it will print: Python is fantastic
    myfunc()
    print("Python is " + x) -->it will print:Python is awesome
  --global keyword: the variable belongs to the global scope
    def myfunc():
      global x
      x = "fantastic"
    myfunc()
    print("Python is " + x) -->now it will print:Python is fantastic
